## 🚨 CRITICAL: TEMPLATE CREATION PROCESS

### **Phase 1: Template Analysis** (AI Reference Only)
1. **Extract Design Data** - From Figma or existing page
2. **Identify Components** - Map design elements to AEM components
3. **Analyze Structure** - Determine template hierarchy
4. **Extract Content** - Get default content and structure
5. **Map Responsive Behavior** - Identify breakpoints and layouts

### **Phase 2: Template Generation** (AI Reference Only)
1. **Create Template Structure** - Generate template files
2. **Configure Policies** - Set up component and layout policies
3. **Generate Initial Content** - Create sample content structure
4. **Set Up Responsive Design** - Configure breakpoints and layouts
5. **Configure Permissions** - Set up user group access

### **Phase 3: Template Validation** (AI Reference Only)
1. **Validate Structure** - Ensure template follows AEM best practices
2. **Test Responsive Design** - Verify breakpoints work correctly
3. **Validate Policies** - Ensure policies are properly configured
4. **Test Content Creation** - Verify template can create pages
5. **Validate Permissions** - Ensure access control works

